.TH "ufshcd_host_memory_configure" 9 "ufshcd_host_memory_configure" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ufshcd_host_memory_configure \- configure local reference block with memory offsets
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ufshcd_host_memory_configure
.BI "(struct ufs_hba *hba "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hba" 12
per adapter instance
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Configure Host memory space
1. Update Corresponding UTRD.UCDBA and UTRD.UCDBAU with UCD DMA
address.
2. Update each UTRD with Response UPIU offset, Response UPIU length
and PRDT offset.
3. Save the corresponding addresses of UTRD, UCD.CMD, UCD.RSP and UCD.PRDT
into local reference block.
